div.div:
Checks if the request.currency is the same as the price.currency. If so, then it does nothing.
If the currencies are different then it invokes the currency service and checks if there is an exchangeRate defined between the currencies. If so, then it recalculates theoriginalValue and theeffectiveValue based on the exchange rate. If the exchangeRate is not defined, then itrejects the price from further processing.

div.div:
Prepares tax calculation request:
sourceTax class is taken from price.location.countryCode
targetTax is taken from request.targetLocation
includesTax is taken from priceModel.includesTax field
If any of the tax classes are not defined then it rejects the price.
Tax service returns a response which contains information about net and gross value.

div.div:
If target includesTax is true (siteSettings.includesTax, if not defined then priceModel.includesTax), then agross value is set to originalValue and effectiveValue.
Otherwise a net value is used for originalValue and effectiveValue.
If any error occurs during tax calculation the price is rejected.
For example: if tax rate is not defied, then itrejects the price from further processing.

div.div:
Gets therequest.quantity and thepriceModel.measurementUnit and converts the unit if needed
(for example kilograms to grams).
Calculates thetotalValue as (effectiveValue * requestQuantity / priceQuantity).
For example: effectiveValue 1.99, requestQuantity 1.2 kg,
priceQuantity 100g => 1.99 * 1200 / 100 = 23.88
